<h1>Ti.CoreMotion</h1>

Ti.CoreMotion allows you to use a few of the CoreMotion native functionality in your Titanium project.


<h2>Before you start</h2>
* This iOS native module designed to work with Titanium SDK 3.2.0.GA
* iOS 7+ is required
* Before using this module you first need to install the package. If you need instructions on how to install a 3rd party module please read this installation guide.

<h2>Download the compiled release</h2>

Download the platform you wish to use:

* [iOS Dist](https://github.com/benbahrenburg/Ti.CoreMotion/tree/master/iOS/dist)

<h2>Building from source?</h2>

If you are building from source you will need to do the following:

Import the project into Xcode:

* Modify the titanium.xcconfig file with the path to your Titanium installation



<h2>Setup</h2>

* Download the latest release from the releases folder ( or you can build it yourself )
* Install the ti.sq module. If you need help here is a "How To" [guide](https://wiki.appcelerator.org/display/guides/Configuring+Apps+to+Use+Modules). 
* You can now use the module via the commonJS require method, example shown below.


